            "id": "688bd95e09622700019c4f29",
            "title": "$100 Invested In Intuit 20 Years Ago Would Be Worth This Much Today",
            "description": "<div><div class=\"sc-ciOwKA eQKRvK\"><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Intuit <span class=\"ticker\" data-exchange=\"NASDAQ\" data-ticker=\"INTU\" style=\"display:inline-block\">INTU</span> has outperformed the market over the past 20 years by 10.64% on an annualized basis producing an average annual return of 19.15%. Currently, Intuit has a market capitalization of $219.08 billion. </p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Buying $100 In INTU:</strong> If an investor had bought $100 of INTU stock 20 years ago, it would be worth <strong>$3,336.72</strong> today based on a price of $785.40 for INTU at the time of writing.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-hmmYps csiXRL\"><div><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-2\"><div class=\"font-semibold\">Trending Investment Opportunities</div><div class=\"flex items-end justify-end\"><div class=\"text-right text-sm bg-gray-200 rounded px-2 py-1\">Advertisement</div></div></div></div><div class=\"cta-stacked GalleryCarousel_splide_slidewrap__zHpTC\"><div class=\"sc-cwcSVF hlcLHF carousel-container\"><div aria-label=\"Carousel\" class=\"splide\"><div class=\"splide-track-wrapper\"><div class=\"splide__track\"><ul class=\"splide__list\"><li class=\"splide__slide\"><div class=\"sc-ePKekS icxejb call-to-action vertical vertical\"></div></li><li class=\"splide__slide\"><div class=\"sc-ePKekS icxejb call-to-action vertical vertical\"></div></li><li class=\"splide__slide\"><div class=\"sc-ePKekS icxejb call-to-action vertical vertical\"></div></li><li class=\"splide__slide\"><div class=\"sc-ePKekS icxejb call-to-action vertical vertical\"></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"carousel-pagination\"><div class=\"splide__arrows\"><button class=\"sc-gUMLBR dFGHQt primary md splide__arrow splide__arrow--prev page-left-button\" type=\"button\"><span><div><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"leading-none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1\" style=\"height:1em;width:1em\" viewbox=\"0 0 320 512\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M15 239c-9.4 9.4-9.4 24.6 0 33.9L207 465c9.4 9.4 24.6 9.4 33.9 0s9.4-24.6 0-33.9L65.9 256 241 81c9.4-9.4 9.4-24.6 0-33.9s-24.6-9.4-33.9 0L15 239z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg></div></span></button><button class=\"sc-gUMLBR dFGHQt primary md splide__arrow splide__arrow--next page-right-button\" type=\"button\"><span><div><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"leading-none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1\" style=\"height:1em;width:1em\" viewbox=\"0 0 320 512\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M305 239c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9L113 465c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l175-175L79 81c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0L305 239z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg></div></span></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--/$--><!--$--><h3 class=\"block core-block\">Intuit's Performance Over Last 20 Years</h3><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-jojPui frsiXV core-image flex items-center justify-center\"><span style=\"background:none;border:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;height:initial;margin:0;opacity:1;overflow:hidden;padding:0;width:initial;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"background:none;border:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:initial;margin:0;opacity:1;padding:0;width:initial;max-width:100%\"><img alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMTUwMCIgaGVpZ2h0PSI4MDAiIHhtbG5zPSJodHRwOi8vd3d3LnczLm9yZy8yMDAwL3N2ZyIgdmVyc2lvbj0iMS4xIi8+\" style=\"background:none;border:0;display:block;height:initial;margin:0;max-width:100%;opacity:1;padding:0;width:initial\"/></span><img alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" style=\"border:none;bottom:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:0;left:0;margin:auto;max-height:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;min-width:100%;padding:0;position:absolute;right:0;top:0;width:0;object-fit:contain\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 1500px, (min-width: 800px) 1500px\" src=\"https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1753995615_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=3840\" srcset=\"https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1753995615_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=1920 1x, https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1753995615_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=3840 2x\" style=\"border:none;bottom:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:0;left:0;margin:auto;max-height:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;min-width:100%;padding:0;position:absolute;right:0;top:0;width:0;object-fit:contain\"/></noscript></span></div><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Finally -- what's the point of all this? The key insight to take from this article is to note how much of a difference compounded returns can make in your cash growth over a period of time.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><em>This article was generated by Benzinga's automated content engine and reviewed by an editor.</em></p><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-dGJnDi fsipWW\"></div><!--/$--></div></div>",
